HEADWORD: Immeasurableness
<hw>Im*meas"ur*a*ble*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The state or quality
of being immeasurable.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Eternity and <qex>immeasurableness</qex> belong to thought
alone.</q> <rj><qau>F. W. Robertson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Immeasurably</ent>⟦br⟧
